        "comment": {
            "name": "comment",
            "type": "com.atlassian.jira.issue.fields.CommentSystemField",
            "value": [
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/45483",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=ggilbert",
                        "name": "ggilbert",
                        "displayName": "Greg",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Bart, just to clarify: the problem isn't in the NotEmpty validator - it's in the one following it.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=ggilbert",
                        "name": "ggilbert",
                        "displayName": "Greg",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2011-03-10T19:43:42.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2011-03-10T19:43:42.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/45485",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=mcleod@spaceweb.nl",
                        "name": "mcleod@spaceweb.nl",
                        "displayName": "Bart McLeod",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Thanks for watching! I realize the problem is in the combination. However, when I put together a UnitTest to verify the bug, I use a very simple form with two fields and a NotEmpty validator on the first element. Nothing else, just to isolate the problem you described.\r\n\r\nTo my surprise, the form validates regardless of the values passed into it. So I now have a problem: is that a bug or something I am doing wrong in the test. In any case, it is obviously not the best way to test, because it involves a form, which does not give us the desired isolation level for this test.\r\n\r\nThen I also wondered what Zend_Filter_Input actually does in this context? Are you using the validators to configure the input filter? You probably do, so I will have to narrow my test function around this scenario. It is also something I did not do before, so my next step will be figuring out the desired behavior with validators that do work.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=mcleod@spaceweb.nl",
                        "name": "mcleod@spaceweb.nl",
                        "displayName": "Bart McLeod",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2011-03-11T00:34:24.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2011-03-11T00:35:49.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/45535",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=mcleod@spaceweb.nl",
                        "name": "mcleod@spaceweb.nl",
                        "displayName": "Bart McLeod",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "I created a unit test for this issue that should reproduce it, but it passes. So I will resolve this as 'not a bug'.\r\n\r\nIt did not look into the default options being ignored. There are also quite a few other 'issues' I encountered during testing that I would like to investigate further.\r\n\r\nHere is my unit test:\r\n{code}\r\n\/**\r\n * @group ZF-11142\r\n *\/\r\npublic function testTwoValidatorsInChainShowCorrectError()\r\n{\r\n    require_once 'Zend\/Validate\/NotEmpty.php';\r\n    require_once 'Zend\/Validate\/Float.php';\r\n    $validators = array(\r\n        'field1'    => array(\r\n                'NotEmpty', 'Float',\r\n                'presence'  => 'required',\r\n                'messages'  => array(\r\n                    'Field1 is empty',\r\n                    array(\r\n                        Zend_Validate_Float::NOT_FLOAT => \r\n                        \"Field1 must be a number.\"\r\n                    )\r\n                )\r\n            ),\r\n        'field2'    => array(\r\n                'presence' => 'required'\r\n            )\r\n    );\r\n    \r\n    $data = array('field1' => 0.0, 'field2' => 'text');\r\n    $input = new Zend_Filter_Input(null, $validators, $data);\r\n    $input->hasValid();\r\n    $messages = $input->getMessages();\r\n    $this->assertSame(  'Field1 is empty', \r\n                        $messages['field1'][Zend_Validate_NotEmpty::IS_EMPTY], \r\n                        'custom message not shown');\r\n    $this->assertSame(0, count($messages['field2']));\r\n}\r\n\r\n{code}",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=mcleod@spaceweb.nl",
                        "name": "mcleod@spaceweb.nl",
                        "displayName": "Bart McLeod",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2011-03-16T22:06:18.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2011-03-16T22:06:18.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/45536",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=mcleod@spaceweb.nl",
                        "name": "mcleod@spaceweb.nl",
                        "displayName": "Bart McLeod",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "resolved as not an issue",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=mcleod@spaceweb.nl",
                        "name": "mcleod@spaceweb.nl",
                        "displayName": "Bart McLeod",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2011-03-16T22:07:28.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2011-03-16T22:07:28.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/45538",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=mcleod@spaceweb.nl",
                        "name": "mcleod@spaceweb.nl",
                        "displayName": "Bart McLeod",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "I read more carefully in the bug description (again) and I added a second test that actually confirms the bug. Sorry for the confusion.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=mcleod@spaceweb.nl",
